gantt
Section Mix the Dressing
In a small bowl, combine 2 TBSP peanut butter, juice of one lime, 1/2 TSP sriracha hot sauce, 1/2 TSP fish sauce, 1 TSP toasted sesame oil, 1 TBSP fresh grated ginger, 1 tsp flaky sea salt :a, 2010-01-01, 1d
Whisk until smooth :b, after a, 1d
Section Assemble the Salad
Wash 1 bunch of kale, remove stems, chiffonade into ribbons and place in a large salad bowl :c, after b, 5d
Peel and shave one large carrot and add to kale mixture :d, after b, 5d
Peel and thinly slice one shallot and add to kale mixture :e, after b, 5d
Crush 1/4 cups roasted unsalted peanuts :f, after b, 2d
Add dressing to kale mixture and massage kale with your hands :g, after b e, 2d
Top with crushed peanuts and serve :h, after f g, 1d
&&&
**Salad**
1 bunch kale, stems removed, and chiffonade into ribbons
1 medium carrot, peeled and shredded/shaved
1/3 cup thinly sliced shallot
1/4 cup crushed roasted, unsalted peanuts
**Dressing**
2 Tbsp. creamy peanut butter
juice of one lime (approx. 2 Tbsp.)
1/2 tsp. Sriracha hot sauce
1/2 tsp. fish sauce
1/2 tsp. sesame oil
1" fresh ginger, grated on a microplane
Sea salt to taste
